pageDescription: Bytes actions are functions that make it easier to work with arrays of bytes and transform them into different formats.

summary.text:
Converts the given [Base64](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base64) string into a byte array that contains the data represented by the string.
Returns the new Uint8Array array.

content.text:
```ts
Convert a Base64 string into bytes
const data = bytes.fromBase64String('aGVsbG8='); // "hello" encoded in Base64
```

summary.text: the Base64 formatted string that should be converted to a Uint8Array byte array.

comment.text:

summary.text:
Converts the given [Data URL](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/web/http/basics_of_http/data_urls) into a blob object.

Returns a blob that contains the binary data. Returns null if the URL is not a valid Data URL.

content.text:
```ts
Convert a data URL to a blob
const blob = bytes.fromBase64Url('data:image/png;base64,aGVsbG8='); // "hello" encoded in Base64
```

summary.text: Converts the given [hexadecimal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hexadecimal) string into a byte array that contains the data represented by the string. Returns the new Uint8Array array.

content.text:
```ts
Convert a hex string into bytes
const data = bytes.fromHexString('fffefd'); // 255, 254, 253 in hex
```

summary.text: the hexadecimal string that should be converted to a byte array.

comment.text: Converts the given [hexadecimal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hexadecimal) string into a byte array that contains the data represented by the string. Returns the new Uint8Array array.

tags.text:


summary.text:
Formats the given bytes into a string that contains the [Base64](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base64) representation of the given data.
Returns the Base64 string.

content.text:
```ts
Format a byte array into Base64
os.toast(bytes.toBase64String(new Uint8Array([ 255, 254, 253 ])));
```

summary.text: Converts the given bytes into a string that contains the [Base64](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base64) [Data URL](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/web/http/basics_of_http/data_urls) representation of the given data.

content.text:
```ts
Convert some bytes to a base 64 image/png data URL
const data = bytes.toBase64Url(new Uint8Array([ 255, 254, 253 ]));
```

```ts
Convert a base 64 string to a text/plain base 64 data URL
const data = bytes.toBase64Url('aGVsbG8=', 'text/plain'); // "hello" encoded in Base64
```

summary.text: The data that should be converted to a Base64 Data URL. If given a string, then it should be valid Base 64 data.

The [MIME Type](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Basics_of_HTTP/MIME_types) of the data.
